  "prompt": "Which is the best recommended book for CA-CPT?",
  "response": "The **CA-CPT (Common Proficiency Test)** is the entry-level examination for becoming a Chartered Accountant in India. It covers four main subjects: **Accounting**, **Mercantile Laws**, **General Economics**, and **Quantitative Aptitude**. While there is no single \"best\" book for CA-CPT, the most recommended study materials are from **The Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI)**. Here are the key resources:\n\n### 1. **ICAI Study Materials**\n   - These are the **official study materials** provided by ICAI and are considered the most reliable and comprehensive for CA-CPT preparation.\n   - They cover the entire syllabus in a structured manner and include practice questions.\n\n### 2. **CA-CPT Scanner by ICAI**\n   - This book contains **past year question papers**, which are invaluable for understanding the exam pattern and practicing questions.\n\n### 3. **Supplementary Books**\n   While ICAI materials are sufficient, some students prefer supplementary books for better understanding or practice. Popular ones include:\n\n   - **Accounting:**\n     - **\"Accounting for CA-CPT\" by P.C. Tulsian**\n     - **\"Fundamentals of Accounting for CA-CPT\" by M.L. Agarwal**\n   - **Mercantile Laws:**\n     - **\"Mercantile Law for CA-CPT\" by P.K. Goel**\n   - **General Economics:**\n     - **\"Economics for CA-CPT\" by H.L. Ahuja**\n   - **Quantitative Aptitude:**\n     - **\"Quantitative Aptitude for CA-CPT\" by R.S. Aggarwal**\n     - **\"Fast Track Objective Arithmetic\" by Rajesh Verma**\n\n### 4. **Practice Books and Mock Tests**\n   - **\"CA-CPT Practice Manual\" by ICAI**: Contains a variety of questions for practice.\n   - **Mock Test Series**: Many coaching institutes like **Jyoti\u2019s Classes**, **Vidya Sagar**, and **PACE** offer mock test series for CA-CPT.\n\n### Tips for Choosing Books:\n- Stick to the **ICAI materials** as the primary source since they are exam-oriented and cover the syllabus thoroughly.\n- Use supplementary books for additional practice or if you need more explanation on difficult topics.\n- Solve past year papers and mock tests to improve time management and accuracy.\n\nRemember, consistent practice and understanding concepts are key to cracking CA-CPT. Good luck!",
